File: Embattled power utility Eskom says the outages are part of efforts to protect its power system from a total collapse. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom has warned of a high possibility of outages throughout Friday. WATCH: Eskom: Pay up or face dark Christmas The utility terminated its stage 2 rotational load-shedding at 5am Friday morning, 6 hours after the initial planned outage time. This is due to unplanned breakdowns and low water levels at its pumped storage schemes among other issues. READ: Eskom: Pay up or face dark Christmas It says the outages are part of efforts to protect its power system from a total collapse. Consumers have been urged to check their load shedding schedules on the Eskom or municipal websites.